-- Canadian March Existing Home Sales Rise 2.5%, Realtors Say
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-04-16T13:56:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/canadian-march-existing-home-sales-rise-2-5-realtors-say-1-.html
Canadian existing home sales rose
2.5 percent in March from the previous month, the  Canadian Real
Estate Association  said.  Sales of 40,356 units were led by gains in Toronto, Calgary
and Edmonton, the Ottawa-based realtor group said. Average
prices fell 1.7 percent to C$367,821 ($367,858), led by an 11.3
percent drop in Vancouver.  From a year earlier, sales rose 1.6 percent, the smallest
gain since April 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
